        "issueNumber": 33299,
        "issueTitle": "I386-elf cross compilers",
        "body": "I've noticed that `jenkins` did not install `i386-elf-binutil` when testing, so we could not use\r\n\r\n    assert_match \"file format elf32-i386\", shell_output(\"#{Formula[\"i386-elf-binutils\"].bin}/i386-elf-objdump -a test-c.o\")\r\n\r\nfor testing, although it work well on my Mac. Is there any way to specify that `i386-elf-binutils` is necessary during the test? The `i386-elf-binutils` and `i386-elf-gcc` are in this PR. Or should I open PR separately for them?"
      }
